<head>
<title>To Add Sampler</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Add Sampler</h1>
<ol>
<li>Choose the Add New Sampler option.</li>
<li>Enter the unique alphanumeric ID</li>
<li>Enter a location either as a latitude/longitude pair or as a klm file via the Google Earth user interface.</li>
<li>Select the Water Body containing the Sampler.</li>
<li>Enter the frequencies that water samples will be taken.  If the sampler is for a ground water body, then a licence number needs to be entered.</li>
<li>Enter a monitoring purpose description.</li>
<li>Click the confirm button to confirm the addition of the new Sampler to the database.</li>
</ol>
<p>If any of the entered values are invalid, an error message will be displayed and the sampler will not be added until the errors are corrected. </p>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>


<head>
<title>Add Water Body</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Add Water Body</h1>
<ol>
<li>Choose the Add New Water Body option.</li>
<li>Enter the unique name.</li>
<li>Select surface water (a creek or river)or ground water (an aquifer).</li>
<li>Enter the exceedance limits for the parameters to be analysed.</li>
<li>Click the confirm button to confirm the addition to the database.</li>
</ol>
<p>if any of the entered values are invalid, an error message will be displayed and the Water Body will not be added until the errors are corrected.
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>

<head>
<title>To Update Contractor</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Update Contractor</h1>
<ol>
<li>Choose the Update Contractor option.</li>
<li>Select the contractor you wish to update.  Any of the Contractor names, contact names, telephone numbers and email addresses may be amended.</li>
<li>Click the confirm button to confirm the update and update the database.  You can choose not to save the changes by not confirming the update.</li>
</ol>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>


<head>
<title>To Update Sampler</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Update Sampler</h1>
<ol>
<li>Choose the Update Sampler option.</li>
<li>Choose the Sampler you want to change.</li>
<li>Delete a Sampler providing that no Sample data has been added for that Sampler yet.</li>
<li>The location can be changed either by entering a latitude/longitude pair or as a kml file via the Google Earth user interface. 
 <br>The licence number, sampling frequencies and monitoring purpose description may be edited.</li>
<li>Click the confirm button to confirm the update and update the database.</li>
</ol>
<p>If any of the entered values are invalid, an error message will be displayed and the sampler will not be added until errors are corrected. <br>
When a Sampler is deleted, it is removed entirely and does not show up on maps.</p>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>


<head>
<title>To Update Water Body</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Update Water Body</h1>
<ol>
<li>Choose the Update Water Body option.</li>
<li>Select the water body you want to update.</li>
<li>Edit the exceedance limits for the parameters to be analysed.</li>
<li>Click the confirm button to confirm the update and update the database.</li>
</ol>
<p>If any of the entered values are invalid, an error message will be displayed and the Water Body will not be added until the errors are corrected.</p>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
