<head>
<title>To Assign Sampler to Contractor</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Assign Sampler to Contractor</h1>
<ol>
<li>Choose the Assign Sampler to Contractor option.</li>
<li>Select a sampling location and then choose the Contractor to assign it to.</li>
<li>Click on the confirm button to confirm the assignment update to the database.</li>
</ol>
<p>If the Sampler has been previously assigned to another Contractor the assignment is removed from the old Contractor and given to the new Contractor.</p>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>


<head>
<title>To Enter Sampling Frequencies</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Enter Sampling Frequencies</h1>
<ol>
<li>Select a subset of parameters which may be tested at this location.</li>
<li>Enter the frequency at which these parameters will be screened. <br>
Frequency is one of daily, weekly, fortnightly, monthly, half yearly and yearly.</li>
<li>Enter a comprehensive screening frequency which is when all parameters will be screened. <br>
If Sampler is for a ground Water Body then a depth monitoring frequency is entered.</li>
</ol>
<p>All frequencies will be entered for a new Sampler, but any subset of frequencies may be amended</p>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>


<head>
<title>To Manage Exceedance Values</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>To Manage Exceedance Values</h1>
<p>Managing Exceedance Values involves adding or updating Water Body information</p>
<ol>
<li>Set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for PH.</li>
<li>Set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for the electrical conductivity.</li>
<li>Set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for the temperature.</li>
<li>Set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for arsenic. </li>
<li>Set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for oil and grease.</li>
<li>If the Water Body is ground water set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for depth to collar.</li>
<li>If the Water Body is surface water set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for fluoride.</li>
<li>If the Water Body is surface water set both the minimum and the maximum exceedance value for chromium.</li>
<li>Click the confirm button to confirm the addition of the update to the database.</li>
</ol>
<p>All exceedance values will be entered for a new Water Body, but any subset of exceedances may be amended.</p>
<a href="HelpPage.html">Return to Help Page</a>
</body>



